==Influence on other languages==
There are several languages that show Goidelic influence, although they are not Goidelic languages themselves.

[[Shelta language]] is sometimes thought to be a Goidelic language, but is in fact a [[cant (language)|cant]] based on Irish and [[English language|English]], with a primarily English-based [[syntax]].

The [[Bungee language]] in [[Canada]] is an English dialect spoken by [[Métis people (Canada)|Métis]] that was influenced by [[Orkney]] English, [[Scots English]], [[Cree language|Cree]], [[Anishinaabe language|Ojibwe]], and [[Scottish Gaelic]].

[[Beurla Reagaird]] is a cant spoken by Scottish traveling folk, which is to a large extent based on Scottish Gaelic.

[[List of English words of Scottish Gaelic origin|English]] and especially [[Highland English]] have numerous words of both Scottish Gaelic and Irish origin.

